condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section I -F.2 | Description :Throughout Project implementation, the Borrower shall maintain its realterms to the amount assigned in the Borrower's national budget for fiscal year 2010 (similar or increased amount of 2010). |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section I -G | Description :The Borrower, through MSN, shall ensure that the Project is carried outin accordance with the provisions of the GAAP Framework andthe Anti-Corruption Guidelines. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section I E -1.a(i) | Description :Appoint under terms of reference satisfactory to the Bank anindependent auditing firm with qualifications and terms of contractingsatisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section I E 1.b | Description :Appoint under terms of reference satisfactory to the Bank anindependent technical auditing firm with qualifications and terms of contracting satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section I- D 1a and b | Description :Carry out a comprehensive evaluation of Public Health Activitiesand adjust them as necessary, in a manner satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 section I D- 2b | Description :Every year, starting immediately after the Effective date for thefirst year of the Project, and on March 31 thereafter, enter intoa Performance Agreement with each Participating Province. |Frequency :Yearly
